{"paperId": "56cec7ad226600cba536a25590c488888e20db96", "abstract": "Ramsauer et al. (2021) recently pointed out a connection between modern Hopfield networks and attention heads in transformers. In this paper, we extend their framework to a broader family of energy functions which can be written as a difference of a quadratic regularizer and a Fenchel-Young loss (Blondel et al., 2020), parametrized by a generalized negentropy function \u2126 . By working with Tsallis negentropies, the resulting update rules become end-to-end differentiable sparse transformations, establishing a new link to adaptively sparse transformers (Correia et al., 2019) and allowing for exact convergence to single memory patterns. Experiments on simulated data show a higher tendency to avoid metastable states.", "venue": "", "year": null, "citationCount": 3, "influentialCitationCount": 1, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "By working with Tsallis negentropies, the resulting update rules become end-to-end differentiable sparse transformations, establishing a new link to adaptively sparse transformers and allowing for exact convergence to single memory patterns."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.3319632411003113, 1.2579182386398315, -0.025965912267565727, 0.3481864035129547, 0.14931130409240723, 0.23120859265327454, 0.44234880805015564, -0.19422420859336853, -0.1332932412624359, 0.03966982662677765, 0.22252117097377777, 0.7678029537200928, 0.21718372404575348, -0.16868984699249268, 0.09701333194971085, -0.2734881341457367, -1.1722584962844849, -0.15125437080860138, 0.4003644585609436, -0.2660239040851593, 0.216344952583313, -0.24966485798358917, -0.9447534084320068, -0.04425526782870293, -0.1266907900571823, 1.4406077861785889, -0.12528766691684723, 0.35583868622779846, 0.014978848397731781, 0.7022193670272827, 0.5808643698692322, -0.2929117679595947, 0.2525356113910675, 0.26996052265167236, -0.0717478096485138, -0.3709661662578583, 0.56704747676